What is an IoT Gateway?
An IoT Gateway acts as a crucial intermediary bridge that connects local, low-power IoT sensor nodes to the upper-level cloud infrastructure or centralized servers. It performs several vital functions:
Protocol Translation: Converts local, short-range IoT protocols used by sensors into internet-compatible protocols suited for the cloud.
Data Filtering & Aggregation: Pre-processes raw sensor data locally to reduce bandwidth consumption before transmission.
Security & Device Management: Provides a localized security barrier, managing authentication and data encryption for constrained devices that cannot handle heavy cryptographic tasks themselves.
